SIMPLE: titter
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Titter
<hw>Tit"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Tittered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Tittering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Probably of imitative
origin.]</ety> <def>To laugh with the tongue striking against the root
of the upper teeth; to laugh with restraint, or without much noise; to
giggle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A group of <qex>tittering</qex> pages ran before.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Titter
<hw>Tit"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A restrained laugh.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧There was a <xex>titter</xex> of . . . delight on his
countenance.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Titter
<hw>Tit"ter</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To seesaw. See
<er>Teeter</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titterel</ent>⟦br⟧
